<font color="#FF0000">THE NEXT GENERATION</font><br>
<tt>Mon Jul 28 23:01:06 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
It's amazing that now as a married woman, being raised from a Mom at home, doing &quot;women&quot; duties and a Dad who worked outside of the home how it has affected my marriage.  I own my own business with my husband and we are struggling to make the change of sharing what used to be considered a &quot;woman's&quot; job in the home.  We want to raise a generation unlike our own experiences by sharing and not demanding and loving unconditionally.  If we are able to raise our children teaching them values that support the opposite sex versus trying to see who can get to the top first and not caring if we hurt the people around us in the process can you imagine the power in this type of generation.  Both sexes would be able to reach their highest potential.<br>
--(Anonymous)<br>

